#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:121
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Authorization is another security aspect of Infinispan. In previous "
"versions, setting up authorization was complicated by the need to add all "
"the needed roles to each cache:"
msgstr ""
"認証は Infinispan "
"のもう一つのセキュリティの側面です。以前のバージョンでは、各キャッシュに必要なすべてのロールを追加する必要があるため、認証の設定が複雑でした。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<infinispan>\n"
"   <cache-container name=\"default\">\n"
"      <security>\n"
"         <authorization>\n"
"            <identity-role-mapper/>\n"
"            <role name=\"AdminRole\" permissions=\"ALL\"/>\n"
"            <role name=\"ReaderRole\" permissions=\"READ\"/>\n"
"            <role name=\"WriterRole\" permissions=\"WRITE\"/>\n"
"            <role name=\"SupervisorRole\" permissions=\"READ WRITE EXEC "
"BULK_READ\"/>\n"
"         </authorization>\n"
"      </security>\n"
"      <distributed-cache name=\"secured\">\n"
"         <security>\n"
"            <authorization roles=\"AdminRole ReaderRole WriterRole "
"SupervisorRole\"/>\n"
"         </security>\n"
"      </distributed-cache>\n"
"   </cache-container>\n"
"   ...\n"
"</infinispan>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:146
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"With Infinispan 11 you can avoid specifying all the roles at the cache level:"
" just enable authorization and all roles will implicitly apply. As you can "
"see, the cache definition is much more concise:"
msgstr ""
"Infinispan 11 では、キャッシュレベルですべてのロールを指定する必要がありません。ご覧のように、キャッシュの定義はより簡潔になりました。"

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<infinispan>\n"
"   <cache-container name=\"default\">\n"
"      ...\n"
"      <distributed-cache name=\"secured\">\n"
"         <security>\n"
"            <authorization/>\n"
"         </security>\n"
"      </distributed-cache>\n"
"   </cache-container>\n"
"   ...\n"
"</infinispan>\n"
msgstr ""

